  "notes": "AST adequacy: lossy — 'a long time' plus 'at every moment it is still happening, with no time when it stops' approximates ceaselessness, but the primes cannot state the universal 'at no point interrupted' cleanly, so the no-break condition reads as a bounded negation rather than a strict all-times quantification."
